    "Adding more layers to the model can lead DNNs to perform better by learning more complicated correlations between the input and output data Benkendorf and Hawkins (2020); López et al (2022).",
    "However, adding too many layers may negatively impact the model's performance through overfitting, which can possible to be solved by applying regularization methods and a validation set.",
    "Nevertheless, adding more layers does not necessarily optimize the DNN's performance.",
    "In some circumstances, it is preferable to utilize a different type of activation function or to increase the number of neurons in each layer.",
    "The best strategy to enhance the DNN's performance is to experiment with various hyperparameters."
